cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a new framework for semi-supervised learning using deep learning techniques. The paper focuses on image classification tasks and uses the ImageNet dataset for evaluation. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of language models for text classification, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper proposes a new training strategy, which involves iterative prediction, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
